{
  "texts": [
    "Among these users, only 1.4% of them are identified as bots (botometer score higher than 3), and 4.2% are close to being classified as bots (botometer score between 2 and 2.5).",
    "Overall, our analysis provides a longitudinal view of the online news consumption landscape in the selected countries, highlighting the predominance of reliable news sources while also revealing the presence of clusters with a higher proportion of questionable news sources in many countries and topics.",
    "The existence of such clusters suggests the presence of a group of users consuming content from various questionable sources while avoiding reliable ones.",
    "This behavior is consistent with the potential presence of echo chambers, a phenomenon widely observed in online debates [7, 20, 42].",
    "In this study, we have delved into the evolving dynamics of news production and consumption within the European context."
  ]
}